From: Helge Deller <deller@gmx.de>
Date: Sun, 11 Dec 2022 19:50:20 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] parisc: Align parisc MADV_XXX constants with all other
 architectures
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.1.6
Git-commit: 71bdea6f798b425bc0003780b13e3fdecb16a010

commit 71bdea6f798b425bc0003780b13e3fdecb16a010 upstream.

Adjust some MADV_XXX constants to be in sync what their values are on
all other platforms. There is currently no reason to have an own
numbering on parisc, but it requires workarounds in many userspace
sources (e.g. glibc, qemu, ...) - which are often forgotten and thus
introduce bugs and different behaviour on parisc.

A wrapper avoids an ABI breakage for existing userspace applications by
translating any old values to the new ones, so this change allows us to
move over all programs to the new ABI over time.

Signed-off-by: Helge Deller <deller@gmx.de>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
